# Systematic Review Automation Tool

## Project Identity
- Purpose: automate systematic literature reviews to IEEE-submission-ready manuscripts.
- Backend: Python 3.11+, PydanticAI Graph, SQLite, FastAPI.
- Frontend: React 19, Vite 7, TypeScript, Tailwind 4.
- Package managers: `uv` (Python), `pnpm` (frontend).

## Always-On Engineering Invariants
- Fix process code in `src/`, never patch artifacts under `runs/`.
- No untyped dicts across phase boundaries; use Pydantic models from `src/models/`.
- No LLM-computed statistics; synthesis math must be deterministic (`scipy`/`statsmodels`).
- All I/O is async (`aiosqlite`, `aiohttp`).
- All LLM calls must log model/tokens/cost/latency into `cost_records`.
- Never hardcode model id strings in source code; use `config/settings.yaml`.
- Use `rich` for CLI output.

## Canonical Source-of-Truth Paths
- Runtime and workflow graph: `src/orchestration/workflow.py`
- Typed contracts: `src/models/`
- DB schema and repositories: `src/db/schema.sql`, `src/db/repositories.py`
- Stats and API count precedence: `src/db/source_of_truth.py`
- LLM provider/rate limiting/fallback: `src/llm/`
- Writing and citation grounding: `src/writing/`
- Manuscript contracts: `src/manuscript/contracts.py`
- Export pipeline: `src/export/`
- Web API: `src/web/app.py`
- Frontend typed API/events: `frontend/src/lib/api.ts`
- Operational edge cases: `.cursor/rules/core/gotchas-agent.mdc`

## Runtime and Operations
- PM2 process names are exact: `litreview-api`, `litreview-ui`, `litreview-tunnel`.
- Production URL serves built `frontend/dist/` via FastAPI on port 8001.
- After backend `src/` changes, restart API process before validation.
- After frontend changes for production verification, run frontend build and restart API.

## Workflow and Data Truth
- Use `study_cohort_membership` (`synthesis_eligibility='included_primary'`) as canonical included-study set.
- Use `cost_records` as canonical cost source.
- Use `workflows_registry.db` `db_path` to resolve runtime DB locations; never reconstruct run paths.

## Strict Commit Safety
- Never stage or commit `.env`, `runs/**`, runtime DB files, or generated run artifacts unless explicitly requested.
- Before any commit, verify staged files do not contain secrets or runtime outputs.

## Where Detailed Guidance Lives
- Full architecture and endpoint inventory: `spec.md` and `README.md`.
- Bootstrap and operational checklist: `.cursor/commands/0-session-bootstrap.md`.
- Task-specific deep guidance: `.cursor/skills/**/SKILL.md`.
- Debugging gotchas and historical failure patterns: `.cursor/rules/core/gotchas-agent.mdc`.
